<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19539] Kafka Streams should also purge internal topics based on user commit requests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19539</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Based on &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/79712093/kafka-streams-application-does-not-purge-repartition-topic-records-when-manual-c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/79712093/kafka-streams-application-does-not-purge-repartition-topic-records-when-manual-c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kafka Streams seems to use &quot;delete record request&quot; for internal topic only on regular commit via `commit.interval.ms`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if `commit.interval.ms` is set to a very high value, and users request commits manually via `context.commit()` no purging happens.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
